Background

		Mr. Thomas O. Ryder, also known as Tom, serves as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Reader's Digest Entertainment, Inc. Mr. Ryder served as an Executive Officer at Books Are Fun, Ltd. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of The Reader's Digest Association Inc. (now known as Trusted Media Brands, Inc.)from April 1998 to December 2005 and served as its Chairman of the Board from April 1998 to December 2006. Mr. Ryder served as the President of American Express ... Travel Related Services International, a division of American Express Company from October 1995 to April 1998. From 1984 to 1998, he worked in several roles at American Express. He served as the Chairman of the Board of Directors at Virgin Mobile USA, Inc. from October 2007 to November 2009. He served as an Independent Director at Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide, Inc., the holding Company of Starwood Hotels & Resorts from April 2001 to September 23, 2016. Mr. Ryder has been a Director of Amazon.com, Inc. since November 2002. He serves as a Director of Association of American Publishers Inc. He has been an Independent Director of ILG, Inc. since May 19, 2016. He served as a Director of Quad/Graphics, Inc. since July 2010 until May 15, 2017 and served as its Lead Independent Director. Mr. Ryder served as Lead Independent Director of RPX Corporation until June 13, 2017 and served as its Director since December 2009 until June 13, 2017. He served as a Director of Schoolpop Inc. He served as a Director of The Reader's Digest Association, Inc. since April 1998. He served as a Trustee of Starwood Hotels & Resorts from April 2001 to April 2006. Mr. Ryder received a Bachelor of Arts Degree in Journalism from Louisiana State University in 1966.Read Full Background




